Hard to tell, but you also have a lot of exposed wire connections on that robot, such as on the motor controllers and the battery. All of those exposed metal bits need to be covered in electrical tape or heat shrink, there‚Äôs a nonzero chance you‚Äôre shorting something right now which could be causing some issues.

These connectors are really good and widely used in FIRST, they‚Äôre best used for connecting motors to their controllers safely

@michiganfc in addition to insulating the wires, you should check that all the connections are firm, especially the ones with a screw through them like at the battery, the main breaker and the PDP input. Do a pull-test on all the wire connections to look for loose connections. This is probably not the cause of your problem but you may find a bad connection that will cause you headaches later.
